com.sleepycat.client

Class SHashStats

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sleepycat.client.SHashStats
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    SDatabaseStats

    public class SHashStats
extends java.lang.Object
implements SDatabaseStats
    The SHashStats object is used to return Hash database statistics.

        public long getBFree()
        The number of bytes free on bucket pages.

        The information is only included if the SDatabase.getStats(com.sleepycat.client.STransaction, com.sleepycat.client.SStatsConfig) call was not configured by the SStatsConfig.setFast(boolean) method.

        Returns:
        the number of bytes free on bucket pages

        public int getNumData()
        The number of key/data pairs in the database.

        If the SDatabase.getStats(com.sleepycat.client.STransaction, com.sleepycat.client.SStatsConfig) call was configured by the SStatsConfig.setFast(boolean) method, the count will be the last saved value unless it has never been calculated, in which case it will be 0.

        Returns:
        the number of key/data pairs in the database
